[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    300[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhy These Services[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    301[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    302[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Kinesis Data Streams for the audit-event ingest backbone.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m EHR audit logs, application audit logs, and network logs flow into a Kinesis stream as they're produced. Kinesis handles the volume (a major health system's audit volume runs into tens of millions of events per day), provides ordered delivery for sequence-based analysis, supports replay for backfill and retraining, and integrates cleanly with the downstream Lambda and analytics components.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    303[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    304[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Lambda for ingest, normalization, and enrichment.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Each event source (Epic Audit Log API, Cerner Behavior Tracker, application audit feeds, IdP logs, VPN logs) has its own Lambda that pulls or receives the source-specific format and writes canonical events into the stream. Downstream Lambdas perform identity resolution, schedule enrichment, care-team enrichment, and sensitivity-flag enrichment.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    305[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    306[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon DynamoDB for the user state and case state stores.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Per-user state (current behavioral baseline summary, recent flag counts, recent case history) and per-case state (open investigations, suppression status, evidence pointers) live in DynamoDB. Single-digit-millisecond reads on user lookup; DynamoDB streams trigger downstream re-evaluation when state changes.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    307[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    308[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Neptune for the relationship graph.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The graph of workforce members, patients, encounters, departments, and devices fits Neptune's property-graph model naturally. Gremlin queries support the relationship-based detection logic ("does this user have a documented care relationship with this patient through any encounter, care team, on-call, or order signature path"). Neptune is HIPAA-eligible. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO (TechWriter): verify current HIPAA eligibility status of Amazon Neptune. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    309[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    310[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Timestream for time-series behavioral baselines.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Per-user time-series of access counts, session durations, and resource-type distributions are time-series data. Timestream's storage and query model fit; magnetic-tier retention covers the multi-week baseline window cost-effectively. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO (TechWriter): verify the current HIPAA eligibility status of Amazon Timestream and BAA coverage; some deployments use S3 with Athena instead. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    311[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    312[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon OpenSearch Service for case management, hunt, and SIEM-style analytics.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Privacy-office case data and the searchable archive of all access events live in OpenSearch. OpenSearch supports the kind of ad-hoc query the privacy office needs ("show me every chart access by this user in the last 90 days," "show me every access on this patient's record in the last week, sorted by user role"). Many SIEM products either run on OpenSearch under the hood or integrate with it cleanly.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    313[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    314[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon SageMaker for model training, hosting, and feature management.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The unsupervised detectors (Isolation Forest, autoencoders), the sequence models, and the supervised re-rankers train as SageMaker Training Jobs against historical data in S3, deploy to SageMaker endpoints for inference, and use SageMaker Feature Store for online and offline feature consistency. SageMaker Clarify produces SHAP-based explanations for each scored case.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    315[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    316[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon SageMaker Model Monitor.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Continuously monitors data drift, prediction drift, and (with labels) model quality. Critical for catching baseline drift caused by EHR upgrades, role changes, organizational restructures, and the gradual shift in workforce behavior that affects every monitoring program.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    317[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    318[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Bedrock for case narrative generation.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The case builder hands the structured evidence package to a Bedrock-hosted LLM that produces the investigator-facing narrative ("This user accessed patient X's record at 11:47 p.m. The user shares a last name with the patient and lives on the same street according to HR records. The user is a step-down nurse and was not assigned to the patient's care team. The access included demographics, medications, and the most recent discharge plan, but no order entry or documentation was performed. The session ended after 90 seconds."). Decision support, not decision-making. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO (TechWriter): confirm the current set of HIPAA-eligible Bedrock foundation models. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    319[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    320[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon Comprehend Medical for note and search-text feature extraction.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Some break-glass override reasons and search queries are free text. Comprehend Medical extracts structured information (medications, conditions, anatomy) that feeds into feature engineering. Optional but useful for break-glass-reason analysis.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    321[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    322[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Step Functions for orchestration.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The nightly user-graph rescoring, the case assembly pipeline, and the periodic retraining are multi-step workflows. Step Functions handles orchestration with retry and error handling.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    323[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    324[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon EventBridge for routing.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Detector outputs publish to EventBridge with user context and case-class metadata. Subscribers include the case builder, the SIEM connector, the audit logger, and the metrics collector. The decoupling supports adding new detector or consumer types without touching the existing components.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    325[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    326[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon API Gateway and AWS AppSync for the privacy-office case management UI.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The privacy office's case queue UI consumes data through AppSync (when GraphQL flexibility is needed for the case-detail views) or API Gateway (for simpler integrations). When the organization uses an existing privacy-monitoring vendor (Protenus, FairWarning, etc.), the integration is API-driven and the UI is the vendor's; the AWS-native components feed it through the integration layer.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    327[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    328[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS Glue and Amazon Athena for the data lake.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Historical audit events, enrichment data, and case outcomes live in S3 partitioned by date. Glue catalogs the schema; Athena provides SQL access for ad-hoc analysis and retraining feature extraction.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    329[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    330[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon QuickSight for governance dashboards.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Subgroup-performance dashboards, alert volume by detector type, case throughput, breach notification timing, and program-level operational metrics. Privacy office leadership, infosec leadership, and the audit committee consume these.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    331[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    332[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon S3 for the data lake and audit log archive.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Partitioned by date and event source, encrypted with customer-managed KMS keys. Used by SageMaker for training, Athena for ad-hoc analysis, and as the long-term archive for compliance retention.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    333[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    334[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAWS IAM Identity Center (or external IdP integration).[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The monitoring system itself has multiple roles: privacy-office investigators (read access to case data, write access to outcomes), privacy-office leadership (read access plus reporting), data-science team (training-data access without identifying user data when possible), and operations team (pipeline monitoring without case-data access). Least-privilege per role. The system ironically has to apply the same access-monitoring discipline to itself that it monitors elsewhere.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    335[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    336[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon CloudWatch and AWS X-Ray.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Pipeline health, ingest latency (especially for the EHR audit log feed, where latency directly affects detection speed), and end-to-end traces. Latency budgets matter: the time from "user takes the action" to "case appears in the privacy-office queue" is part of the operational metric.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    337[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
